cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SE 

The paper discusses scaling up machine learning algorithms using memory mapping, which is a technique commonly used in the field of large-scale data processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with out-of-core datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper proposes an approach for existing machine learning algorithms, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the speed of the proposed approach, which could be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
